<REFENTRY id="bc">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>
bc
</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>bc</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
an arbitrary precision calculator language
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>
<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
<COMMAND>bc</COMMAND> is as specified in <XREF LINKEND=STD.SUSv4> but with
extensions as listed below.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Extensions</TITLE>
<PARA>
The bc language may be extended in an implementation defined manner. If an
implementation supports extensions, it shall also support the additional
options:
<VARIABLELIST>

<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>-s|--standard</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
processes exactly the POSIX <command>bc</command> language.
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>

<VARLISTENTRY>
<TERM>-w|--warn</TERM>
<LISTITEM>
<PARA>
gives warnings for extensions to POSIX bc.
</PARA>
</LISTITEM>
</VARLISTENTRY>

</VARIABLELIST>
</para>
</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
